00:02:49.940 --> 00:02:51.060
It is going to be
television show.

00:02:51.060 --> 00:02:53.200
It's going to be set in
this time in this era.

00:02:53.200 --> 00:02:54.960
Who's going to help me make it?

00:02:54.960 --> 00:02:56.480
SAM SHAW: So I wrote a draft.

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:58.280
I revised it.

00:02:58.280 --> 00:03:00.130
I wrote about 20
drafts, and finally it

00:03:00.130 --> 00:03:01.963
became the thing it was
sort of going to be,

00:03:01.963 --> 00:03:05.020
and I partnered up with my
partner in crime creatively,

00:03:05.020 --> 00:03:08.930
Tommy Schlamme, our executive
producer and director,

00:03:08.930 --> 00:03:11.710
who is very well
known in television.

00:03:11.710 --> 00:03:14.340
Won about a million Emmys
for "The West Wing"--

00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:16.180
principally is what
he's known for.

00:03:16.180 --> 00:03:18.724
And then we went looking for
some congenial partners who

00:03:18.724 --> 00:03:20.890
would help us get this thing
made, and first of all,

00:03:20.890 --> 00:03:24.710
it's an incredibly ambitious
and complicated show to make.

00:03:24.710 --> 00:03:25.290
Period.

00:03:25.290 --> 00:03:29.040
Full stop, but particularly
on television, particularly

00:03:29.040 --> 00:03:30.450
on basic cable.

00:03:30.450 --> 00:03:33.860
So finding people who had the
right creative sensibilities,

00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:36.030
who loved this subject
matter and loved the story as

00:03:36.030 --> 00:03:38.600
much as we did-- it
was sort of a miracle

00:03:38.600 --> 00:03:41.404
that we wound up with
the folks on this stage.

00:03:41.404 --> 00:03:43.320
And so we sat down
together, I guess, probably

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:45.650
about-- I don't know--
two and a half years ago

00:03:45.650 --> 00:03:47.670
or something like that.

00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:50.465
It was this very refreshing
thing where it was really

00:03:50.465 --> 00:03:52.840
just a few people in the room,
and we talked passionately

00:03:52.840 --> 00:03:55.400
about the subject matter, and
by the end of the meeting,

00:03:55.400 --> 00:03:58.532
they said, let's go make
a TV show, and we did.

00:03:58.532 --> 00:04:00.490
DANA HAN-KLEIN: Was there
anything scary to you

00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.640
guys about the scope of
this television show?

00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:03.640
It's a period piece.

00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:08.314
It's about a very tough
time in US history.

00:04:08.314 --> 00:04:09.480
DAVID ELLISON: Dana, please.

00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:10.690
DANA GOLDBERG: Not really.

00:04:10.690 --> 00:04:14.090
