00:27:40.096 --> 00:27:41.512
MARCY ROSS: Didn't
stand a chance.

00:27:41.512 --> 00:27:41.960
Did not stand a chance.

00:27:41.960 --> 00:27:43.220
DANA HAN-KLEIN: Not necessarily
going to stand a chance,

00:27:43.220 --> 00:27:44.595
but it's great
that you guys have

00:27:44.595 --> 00:27:47.065
found a home for
it, and also, again,

00:27:47.065 --> 00:27:48.430
"Grace and Frankie" on Netflix.

00:27:48.430 --> 00:27:51.670
So you guys have really
embraced this divergence

00:27:51.670 --> 00:27:54.090
of trusting your audience.

00:27:54.090 --> 00:27:55.840
Are there other projects
that you guys are

00:27:55.840 --> 00:27:59.700
excited to work on with that, or
are you incubating these babies

00:27:59.700 --> 00:28:00.200
right now?

00:28:00.200 --> 00:28:01.033
MARCY ROSS: Oh, yes.

00:28:01.033 --> 00:28:04.260
No, I have to say this is an
amazing time for television.

00:28:04.260 --> 00:28:07.560
I've been in the business--
in the conventional television

00:28:07.560 --> 00:28:09.880
business, for over 20 years.

00:28:09.880 --> 00:28:14.790
So for me to look
out at the wild west,

00:28:14.790 --> 00:28:17.310
and there's 57 places
to sell content,

00:28:17.310 --> 00:28:21.150
and there's so many
different ways to communicate

00:28:21.150 --> 00:28:24.430
your specific vision for a show,
or to have a writer like Sam,

00:28:24.430 --> 00:28:28.460
or Marta Kauffman,
or we're working

00:28:28.460 --> 00:28:31.190
with some other
fantastic writers,

00:28:31.190 --> 00:28:34.677
and basically sit with them
and say, what you want to do?

00:28:34.677 --> 00:28:36.510
Don't think about where
you want to sell it.

00:28:36.510 --> 00:28:40.490
Don't think about what
the potential of it

00:28:40.490 --> 00:28:43.200
is in terms of business,
but just you do it,

00:28:43.200 --> 00:28:46.690
and you do it as best and with
most integrity that you can,

00:28:46.690 --> 00:28:48.530
and we will find a home for it.

00:28:48.530 --> 00:28:52.030
You never used to be
able to program that way.

00:28:52.030 --> 00:28:54.900
So it's creative drives
everything right now,

00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:57.057
and that is
incredibly liberating.

00:28:57.057 --> 00:28:58.640
DANA HAN-KLEIN: As
an audience member,

00:28:58.640 --> 00:28:59.764
that's always nice to hear.

00:28:59.764 --> 00:29:01.290
MARCY ROSS: No, it's wonderful.

00:29:01.290 --> 00:29:02.710
